[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] which does not check the input or output types.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] This still does parse the query to ensure it’s syntactically and semantically valid for the current database.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] where the SQL query is stored in a separate file.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] which does not typecheck bind parameters and leaves the output type to inference.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] The query itself is still checked that it is syntactically and semantically valid for the database, that it only produces one column and that the number of bind parameters is correct.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] Capable of being used in place of any SQLx database driver.
[src:sqlx-rust/latest-sqlx] The actual driver used will be selected at runtime, from the connection url.
